CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1941, pg. 10 reads: "Charming Youth Was About During Holidays - Charming youth was prevalent at all of the parties. Here is a pretty trio at one of the events.  Left to right: Muriel Lewis, Jane Ribeau, Jean Sherrow. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Muriel Lewis (Bridges), Jane Ribeau, and Jean Sherrow with legs crossed, seated in interior
